A good product nonetheless if you intend to use for a year or two at decentish price.

Bought it about 2 weeks ago and have been using it for a while. While most of the reviews here found it good, I didn't. For me, the product felt not well-engineered. The axes of the hinges are not sturdy and the handles kept slipping from their holes whenever I had to do micro-adjustments to the laptop. Don't get me wrong -- the stand handles any weight of the laptop because it's made from metal and can give the keyboard a much needed slope to make it easy to write. But the lack of sturdyness of the stand and the small width of the stand make typing hard because the laptop felt wobbly. If you are going to attach an external keyboard, then this product might be a good buy as you won't be touching a laptop. But, if you are going to be typing on the laptop then you are going to not like it.PS: My laptop is a 15.6 inch laptop and I bought this laptop mainly so that the keyboard will feel inclined and the sharp edges of the laptop wont hurt my hand.
